<p><b>Balthasar Kłossowski de Rola</b> (February 29, 1908 in Paris – February 18, 2001 in <a href="/wiki/Rossini%C3%A8re" title="Rossinière">Rossinière</a>, Switzerland), known as <b>Balthus</b> (pronounced "Bal-TOOSS"), was an esteemed but controversial Polish/French <a href="/wiki/Modern_art" title="Modern art">modern artist</a>.</p>
